  "title": "Relief- Infant Educator (EY1/ EY2) [Hougang]",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p>Attends to the basic needs of a group of 2 months to 17 months</p><p>Works together with parents in assessing children’s developmental growth</p><p>Ensures children’s safety & well-being while under the centre’s care</p><p>Implements centre’s programmes and new initiatives</p><p><br /><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum Higher Certificate in Infant Care (HCIC) or Advanced Certificate in Early Years (ACEY)</li><li>EY1/EY2 LON from ECDA preferred but not mandatory (Entry level EC candidates welcomed to apply)</li><li>Possess a positive working attitude and have the drive to nurture early learners</li><li><strong>Staying in North-East/ North/ East Singapore</strong></li></ul><p><u><strong>Location</strong></u></p><ul><li>Blk 967 Hougang Avenue 9</li></ul><p><u><strong>Working Hours</strong></u></p><ul><li>Rotating Shifts</li><li>5-day work week per month</li><li>Centre operates from 7am to 7.30pm (Monday to Friday) and 7am to 2pm (Saturday)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Hourly Salary:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>$15.00 – $18.00 per hour</strong> (Commensurate with experience and qualifications)</li></ul><p></p>",
